      Know When You Are Needed

      Get Notified Anywhere

      Get instant notifications from your phone every time your baby is awake or fussy.

      Gain Peace of Mind at a Glance

      The base glows green to indicate that your baby is doing fine. A sound and a red light from the base lets you know that you should check on your baby.

      More Accurate Readings

      By using a Fresnel lens, infrared light can be refracted better for stronger optical signals for accurate measurements.

      The Softest Touch

      Made from breathable, washable material, Smart Sock can be worn on either foot and comes in three sizes, fitting babies up to 18 months or 30 lbs.

      Long-Lasting Battery

      The long battery life of eufy Baby Smart Sock enables up to 24 hours of tracking on a single charge so you can have a good night's sleep.

      Wireless Charging

      The base also serves as a charging pad. Strong magnets hold the sensor on the sock in place while it charges, so you can just drop it and go.

      What's In the Box：Sensor; Socks × 3; Base; Power Adapter; Power Cable; Quick Start Guide

      Notes: 1.Based on the test results of the eufy Baby lab. 2. All images are for illustration purposes only. 3. Disclaimer: eufy Baby Smart Sock is not a medical device. It is designed and intended to provide insights into your baby's sleep patterns and help with your baby's general sleep habits. Smart Sock is not intended to and cannot be used to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease or condition, including but not limited to, sudden infant death syndrome (SIDS).

      FAQ

      Q: Why does my baby have red marks on their feet after wearing Smart Sock S320? A: A baby's skin is very sensitive and delicate. Prolonged use of smart socks in high temperatures or humid environments may lead to red marks or imprints. Additionally, if a baby frequently kicks, the continuous friction could cause localized abrasions or even blisters. If this occurs, please check the following: -- Ensure you have chosen the correct sock size. -- Make sure your baby's feet, and Smart Sock S320, are clean and dry. -- Ensure there are no open wounds on your baby's feet. For more details, check the blog in the app.

      Q: Is eufy Baby Smart Sock safe for my baby? A: Yes, eufy Baby Smart Sock is safe for daily use with your baby when used as instructed. The sensor tracks your baby's sleep via light reflections (PPG technology) and baby's movements. The sock uses high-quality fabric that wraps comfortably on your baby's feet. All components of the smart sock are carefully selected and manufactured with quality in mind. We have collaborated with parents like you and engaged in rigorous tests to make sure the sock is safe for all.

      Q: Does the device generate any radio emmisions that would harm my baby? A: Smart Sock is not harmful to the baby as it has been tested and meets the applicable limits for radio frequency (RF) exposure. The sock connects with the base periodically via Bluetooth Low Energy 5.0 (2.4GHz) that has low power output. The base and camera connect to your phone via Wi-Fi like any other Wi-Fi-connected devices in your room.

      Q: Will Smart Sock cause a choking hazard to my baby? A: Smart Sock is safe for your baby and meets the safety standards. As a precaution, keep the sock sensor away from your baby's mouth.

      Q: Why doesn't the product send alerts or notifications? A: The sock alerts you for low battery, Bluetooth disconnection, and improper wearing. To receive these notifications, make sure to choose the correct sock size and that it's worn properly.

      Q: How does Smart Sock track my baby's sleep? A: Our sleep algorithm detects the baby's current sleep state based on movements and heart rate. You can use the sock to track daytime naps and nighttime sleep. External activities will affect sleep detection, such as sleeping in a moving stroller, in a car, in a moving bassinet, or being carried in your arms. The sleep detection algorithm best suits a baby sleeping in a bed/crib.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        5.0 out of 5 stars GET THIS... Not the Owlet!
        Reviewed in the United States on February 28, 2025
        Verified Purchase
        This sock is a significant improvement over the Owlet! Every issue the Owlet had has been addressed and enhanced with this design, making it a far superior option.

        The most significant difference is the ability to customize alerts, allowing you to adjust how they are received, at what volume, and how frequently. Another key improvement is that this product can be used in separate rooms from the base, providing greater flexibility.

        However, the most notable improvement is the placement of the monitoring probe. This design ensures the sock remains securely in place, making it far more reliable. This addresses a major issue with the Owlet, which often had problems with the sensor shifting out of position.

        The monitor is great give me the information and peace of mind I needed! Additionally it is easy to apply on my baby and it seems to be comfortable for him to use.

        Overall, while this product is expensive and not necessarily essential for everyone, it offers long-term value by providing support through various stages of a baby’s development—particularly during times of uncertainty and anxiety. It is a reliable solution that brings peace of mind when parents need to rest and cannot constantly monitor their baby.

      • Anne + Matt
        5.0 out of 5 stars Great peace of mind
        Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2023
        Verified Purchase
        I couldn’t be happier with this smart sock. Our daughters have had convulsive seizures, so we have multiple monitors to give us peace of mind at night. The Eufy Smart Sock is a great value and has all the features I need. I love that I can set the parameters for notifications and that I can allow it to notify me (audibly) even when my phone is on Do Not Disturb at night.

        I want to highlight one experience. My baby was napping, and I was watching her on a monitor. I saw her start having a seizure, so I rushed in and took care of her. The Eufy notified me that her heart rate was abnormal after she had been seizing for 15 minutes. This may sound like a long time, but if it were the middle of the night, being notified 15 minutes in would be better than not being notified at all. Now I know it will notify me, which brings me greater peace of mind. I set the heart rate range a little lower so I will be notified sooner in the future.

        I know these are not medical devices and I can’t depend on baby monitors to keep my kids safe, but if it can calm my anxiety the tiniest bit, it’s worth the money.
